            <h2>EXTRA-CURRICULAR</h2>
            <h4>Special emphasis is placed on extra=curricular activities, encouraging participation of every child. Most activities are conducted on both Inter-House and Inter-School levels in the form of various contests and competitions. However, some events are solely held to meet the hone the social, physical and mental skill of every child.<br><br>

Spelling Contests, Music and Quiz Contests, Football, Basketball, Table Tennis, Art, Swimming, Board Games are a few that are a regular feature of the Academic Year.<br><br>

Additional field trips and excursions are often a part of the school year, to help break away from the confines of a classroom and help your children experience course related matters first hand. This also gives them a greater understanding of the subjects being taught in class and a chance to build stronger inter-personal skills. </h4>
